Vivid – very clear and detailed
Example: She gave a vivid description of the place.
Gloomy – dark or depressing
Example: The weather looks gloomy today.
Radiant – shining or glowing
Example: She looked radiant in her dress.
Fragile – easily broken
Example: This glass is very fragile.
Analyze – examine in detail
Example: We need to analyze the results.
Infer – to conclude from evidence
Example: I infer that he is happy from his smile.
Concept – an idea or principle
Example: This concept is difficult to understand.
Theory – explanation based on evidence
Example: Einstein proposed the theory of relativity.
